{"lemma":"أَعْفَرانِ","slug":"أَعْفَرانِ","root":"ع.ف.ر","root_slug":"ع-ف-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-ف-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["adj"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n29737"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D8%B9%D9%92%D9%81%D9%8E%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%86%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"ash-gray"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Color or defect adjective from the root ع ف ر (ʕ f r)."},"ipa":["/ʔaʕ.far/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n29737","headword_ar":"اَعْفَرُ","root":"Efr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Dust-coloured inclining to white; of a whitish dust-colour:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"white, but not of a clear hue:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) or, applied to a buckantelope,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"white, but not of a very clear white,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AZ, As, S, O, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"being like the colour of the surface of the earth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AZ, As, Mgh:) or a buck-antelope"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having a tinge of red over his whiteness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AA, S, A, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with a short neck;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and such is the weakest of antelopes in running: (AA, S, O:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having a redness in his back, with white flanks:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) [in the CK, after the words thus rendered, is an omission, of the words"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^awi AlA^aboyaDu wa","text_ar":"اَوِ الاَبْيَضُ وَ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as inhabits elevated, rugged, stony tracts, and hard grounds; and such is red:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AZ:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having white horns:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A:) fem."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaforaA='u","text_ar":"عَفْرَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, K, &c.:) also applied to a she-goat, meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a clear white colour:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuforN","text_ar":"عُفْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, A, O.) ―         -b2-  El-Kumeyt says,"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2091},{"kind":"quote","text":"wakun~aA A_i*aA jab~aAru qawomK A^araAdanaA\n                      \n                     \n                        bikayodK HamalonaAhu EalaY qaroni A^aEofaraA"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And we used, when an insolent tyrant of a people desired to execute against us a plot, to carry him upon the horn of an antelope of a whitish dustcolour,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"white but not of a clear hue,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]; meaning, we used to slay him, and to carry his head upon the spear-head; for the spear-heads, in time past, were of horns. (S, O.) ―         -b3-  Hence the saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ramaAniY Eano qaroni A^aEofara","text_ar":"رَمَانِى عَنْ قَرْنِ اَعْفَرَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rmAnY bidaAhiyapK","text_ar":"رمانى بِدَاهِيَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He sent upon me a calamity;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he made a very crafty man to be my assailant"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: for the same reason, also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaronu A^aEofara","text_ar":"قَرْنُ اَعْفَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is proverbially used to signify (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A difficulty,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"distress, that befalls one:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and one says to a man who has passed the night in disquieting distress,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kunota EalaY qaroni A^aEofara","text_ar":"كُنْتَ عَلَى قَرْنِ اَعْفَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thou wast pierced by grief"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) One says also, of him who is frightened and disquieted,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaA^an~ahu EalaY qaroni A^aEofara","text_ar":"كَاَنَّهُ عَلَى قَرْنِ اَعْفَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is as though he were upon the horn of an antelope of a whitish dustcolour,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.: meaning,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon the head of a spear"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: the like of this phrase is used by Imra-el-Keys. (A.) ―         -b4-  Also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaforaA='u","text_ar":"عَفْرَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", A ewe"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a colour inclining to whiteness."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O.) ―         -b5-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEofaru","text_ar":"اَعْفَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Red"},{"kind":"text","text":"sand. (S, O.) ―         -b6-  [Food of the kind called]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"variyd","text_ar":"ثَرِيد"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made white:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuforapN","text_ar":"عُفْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifying the “ colour of the earth. ” (TA.) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaforaA='u","text_ar":"عَفْرَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"White."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b8-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aroDN EaforaA='u","text_ar":"اَرْضٌ عَفْرَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Untrodden land."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) ―         -b9-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEaforaA='u","text_ar":"العَفْرَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The thirteenth night"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the lunar month"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, O:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the night of blackness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A:) but accord. to IAar,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"All~ayaAliY AlEuforu","text_ar":"اللَّيَالِى العُفْرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the white nights;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A;) and so says Th, without particularizing: (TA:) or the nights thus called are"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the seventh and eighth and ninth nights of the lunar month;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) because of the whiteness of the moon [therein]. (TA.) It is said in a trad."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layosa Euforu All~ayaAliY","text_ar":"لَيْسَ عُفْرُ اللَّيَالِى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaA@ld~aA=diy^i","text_ar":"كَا@لدَّا=دِيِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The moon-lit nights are not like the black nights:"},{"kind":"text","text":"some say that this is a proverb. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["TA","Msb","AZ","As","S","O","K","Mgh","AA","A"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}